{
  "doc_id": "15014",
  "text": "In previous studies, the coupling between a dielectric slab waveguide consisting of a 1.25 μm silica core surrounded by air, and a 50 nm two-dimensional gold-silica-gold MDM plasmonic waveguide has been theoretically investigated [CITATION_1] . A coupling efficiency of ∼70% was demonstrated by using a 2.5 μm long linearly tapered plasmon waveguide coupler. High coupling efficiency between silicon waveguides and metal slot waveguides using 4 μm long linear tapers has also been demonstrated experimentally [CITATION_2] . In addition, efficient coupling between silicon-on-insulator dielectric waveguides and metallic stripe plasmonic waveguides has been demonstrated experimentally for a coupling length of 1.8 μm [CITATION_3] . In contrast, our focus here is on coupling structures either without any transition region between the dielectric and plasmonic waveguides, or with submicron scale transition regions.",
  "correct_citation": {
